Yeah, I like the idea of grouping not based on alignment -- guild or six-groups.  There are some really good reasons for two religions to group up and bash something more threatening (as a good example: Erudite and Heretic should group up and eliminate the kobold threat).<br>
<br>
Buffs should be somewhat religion dependent.  Or perhaps, have faction consequences.  A cleric takes his powers directly from his diety, so using those powers on someone of the opposing alignment should have dire consequences ... like reducing his native faction by a little bit.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, Bards' buffs other int-based casters' buffs are not really related to religion.<br>
<br>
I'm actually wondering how active the dieties are supposed to be.  If it's like Greek myths, then the gods will meddle in our day-to-day lives.  If it's Medieval, then its the religious institutions who actually determine how active they are involved in day-to-day lives.  A Spanish Inquisition might actively hunt down those who buff evil ... but otherwise, who cares? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugolsec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golsec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/19/01 4:29:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/golavatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> On languages</span><hr size=1> The only thing I'd change would be to put back common tongue. After all, the NPCs all speak it anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
