<br>
First... Drop TLC.<br>
Here is why, and remember its just my opinion.  <br>
Its just to much of a problem. For one thing it does not add to roleplaying at all, in fact it forces players to &quot;plan&quot; out their characters with information they obtain from spoiler sites. Also, from what I've seen in-game and read on message boards even most of the people who think it should stay believe it needs to be modified in one way or another. I don't believe Verant will bother to modify it. Even if they do they won't come up with a solution that everyone thinks is good.<br>
<br>
<br>
Second... Alignment changes - add more.<br>
That is I think they should add more flexability at later levels. I'm not saying that a &quot;evil-only&quot; race or religion should ever be allowed to be good. But I could deffinently see a member growing more accustomed (neutral) to other ideas as they learn and advance.<br>
<br>
And thats it. Everything else I would leave the same. Some things I don't particularly like, but I wouldn't change them. For example: I've gone to playing a couple hours a day on my old server just to play around with a Troll Beastlord. I would rather play a Troll Beastlord on FV, but I wouldn't want to add more character slots as doing so would probably screw things up.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, thats what I would change - but no matter what the players want I wouldn't hold my breath waiting for Verant. Even if they wanted to change some things up they probably still have their handsfull with SOL issues.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bardicj>Bardic J</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/19/01 11:09:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On languages</span><hr size=1> Either take all quest items off TLC, or simply remove it altogether.<br>
<br>
Maybe if this server had the population of the others, I could buy the hole &quot;make friends and buy your quest items for the lower levels!&quot; song and dance, but it doesn't and I don't.<br>
<br>
I doubt they will do either though, so we'll just have to deal with it or leave the server.I'm leaning more towards dealing with it at this point.<br>
<br>
I'd also like if Good and Evil could group together, but in turn would recieve no exp for kills. This would make Good and Evil teaming up to kill Dragons and other Common enemies of extreme power common place, but also prevent Good and Evil from &quot;hanging out&quot; together on a day to day basis.<br>
When Grouped good and evil could heal/buff each other, but when not grouped the same rules would apply. <br>
<br>
You could go a step further, to prevent cheating, perhaps make it so as long as you are Buffed by someone opposed to your alignment, you cannot recieve exp, this would stop /invite buff /disband kind of schemes.<br>
<br>
Guilds should have a /alignment connected to them, those too far outside of that alignment could not join.<br>
<br>
More RP GM events ( not really a rule change, just a request)<br>
<br>
Option to change deity /alignment at 30. <br>
<br>
Agnostics/nuetrals must be punished! They have it too easy and its quickly becoming the default choice do to convience.<br>
Give them a exp penalty for grouping with either good or evil.<br>
This would be a penalty to the Nuetral player only, the Evil or good player would receive their normal experience. <br>
<br>
I realize that may upset the many nuets... But its just my opinion there, not as if any of this will ever go into play <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
